"{\"abstract\":\"This paper focuses on structured-output learning using deep neural networks for 3D human pose estimation from monocular images. Our network takes an image and 3D pose as inputs and outputs a score value, which is high when the image-pose pair matches and low otherwise. The network structure consists of a convolutional neural network for image feature extraction, followed by two sub-networks for transforming the image features and pose into a joint embedding. The score function is then the dot-product between the image and pose embeddings. The image-pose embedding and score function are jointly trained using a maximum-margin cost function. Our proposed framework can be interpreted as a special form of structured support vector machines where the joint feature space is discriminatively learned using deep neural networks. We test our framework on the Human3.6m dataset and obtain state-of-the-art results compared to other recent methods. Finally, we present visualizations of the image-pose embedding space, demonstrating the network has learned a high-level embedding of body-orientation and pose-configuration.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"1944369\",\"name\":\"Sijin Li\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1944369\"},{\"authorId\":\"2330776\",\"name\":\"W. Zhang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2330776\"},{\"authorId\":\"3651407\",\"name\":\"Antoni B. Chan\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/3651407\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":\"1910.09070\",\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"2773227\",\"name\":\"E. Aksan\"},{\"authorId\":\"35090707\",\"name\":\"Manuel Kaufmann\"},{\"authorId\":\"2531379\",\"name\":\"Otmar Hilliges\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1109/ICCV.2019.00724\",\"intent\":[],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"1ea66b3985a8ed724ab31dcc35f0319cd720f840\",\"title\":\"Structured Prediction Helps 3D Human Motion Modelling\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/1ea66b398